com.camerontec.catalys.application.marketdata

Interface IDepthEntryUpdateMessage

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IMarketDataMessage, ISetValueStore
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DepthEntryIncrementalDecorator, ReusableDepthEntryUpdateMessage

    public interface IDepthEntryUpdateMessage
extends ISetValueStore, IMarketDataMessage
    All depth entry update messages implement this interface.

    Note that special attributes are supported for entryID, price, quantity and side. These are fields that appear in every depth entry update. See IInstrumentDepthListener depth entry update callback methods. Since each of these standard fields is specified on every update, they do not ever need to be explicitly cleared.

    Other fields which may or may not appear on an update are stored using the ISetValueStore interface (which this extends). That interface does have an explicit clearValues method which must be called prior to each new batch of updates.

    • Method Detail

      • setStandardValues

        void setStandardValues(int entryID,
                       int price,
                       int qty,
                       int side)
        Updates the standard fields associated with a depth entry update.
        Parameters:
        entryID - Entry ID value associated with this update. This will be used to populate a FIX MDEntryID field (see Constants.TAGiMDEntryID)
        price - Price value associated with this update. This will be used to populate a FIX MDEntryPx field (see Constants.TAGiMDEntryPx)
        qty - Quantity value associated with this update. This will be used to populate a FIX MDEntrySize field (see Constants.TAGiMDEntrySize)
        side - Side associated with this update. This will be used to populate a FIX MDEntryType field (see Constants.TAGiMDEntryType). Indicates buy, sell or not specified. 0 - Not specified, 1 - Buy, 2 - Sell.
